title: Home
description: >
  <p>The Groove Library exists to explore rhythm as a global language.</p>

  <p>Born from a decade of Afro-centric digging under the name <a href="/easton-chop-up">Easton Chop Up</a>, The Groove Library expands the lens — reaching across borders, eras and genres to document music built for movement, meaning and connection.</p>

  <p>Through DJ mixes, live streams, guest selectors, album deep-dives and communal listening parties, The Groove Library curates sound as both archive and experience. It is a space for dancers, listeners, collectors and the curious — equally at home in ritual, roots, club systems and future experiments.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Curated by people, not algorithms.</li>
    <li>Spanning cultures, not confined by genre.</li>
    <li>A journey, not a destination.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Only the groove — shared, studied, celebrated and passed forward.</p>
